"720","77m"
"721","Putnam Multi-Cap Growth Fund"
"722","6/30/11 annual report"
"723","Acquisition of Putnam Vista Fund"
"724","On September 27, 2010, the fund issued 21,970,683, 1,494,855,"
"725","488,294, 397,127, 54,165 and 861,908 class A, class B, class C,"
"726","class M, class R and class Y shares, respectively, for"
"727","96,718,304, 6,785,681, 2,156,292, 1,769,923, 238,471 and"
"728","3,764,946 class A, class B, class C, class M, class R and class"
"729","Y shares of Putnam Vista Fund to acquire that funds net assets"
"730","in a tax-free exchange. Putnam Management recommended, and the"
"731","Board of Trustees approved, the merger transaction because it"
"732","believed that it was in the best interests of shareholders of"
"733","Putnam Vista Fund to be invested in a fund with more flexibility"
"734","to invest in attractive companies regardless of capitalization"
"735","size. Putnam Management believed that this flexibility would"
"736","increase the likelihood of delivering strong investment"
"737","performance over the long-term. In addition, after the merger,"
"738","Putnam Vista Fund shareholders would be invested in a larger"
"739","fund with a lower expense ratio. The investment portfolio of"
"740","Putnam Vista Fund, with a fair value of $931,784,799 and an"
"741","identified cost of $870,278,890 at September 24, 2010, was the"
"742","principal asset acquired by the fund. The net assets of the fund"
"743","and Putnam Vista Fund on September 24, 2010, were $2,348,440,346"
"744","and"
"745","$1,118,296,596, respectively. On September 24, 2010, Putnam"
"746","Vista Fund had accumulated net investment loss of $1,279,092,"
"747","accumulated net realized loss of $1,846,121,583 and unrealized"
"748","appreciation of $65,891,595. The aggregate net assets of the"
"749","fund immediately following the acquisition were $3,466,736,942."
"750","Assuming the acquisition had been completed on July 1, 2010, the"
"751","funds pro forma results of operations for the reporting period"
"752","are as follows:"
"753","Net investment loss $(6,981,864)"
"754","Net gain on investments $1,132,847,222"
"755","Net increase in net assets resulting from operations"
"756","$1,125,865,358"
"757","Because the combined investment"
"758","portfolios have been managed as a single portfolio since the"
"759","acquisition was completed, it is not practicable to separate the"
"760","amounts of revenue and earnings of Putnam Vista Fund that have"
"761","been included in the funds statement of operations for the"
"762","current fiscal period."
